description:
Bug 38131ajc needs -d option. I am using 1.1rc1. This is a regression since rc1 and a deviation from javac. I am guessing this may have something to do with a change in the underlying Eclipse compiler.

To reproduce the bug:
1. Create a class in a subpackage such as:

   package subpackage;

   public class Test {
       public static void main(String[] args) {
           System.out.println('Hello');
       }
   }

2. Compile using the following command: ajc subpackage\Test.java

   - Observed Behavior: The test.class file is then put in the subpackage\subpackage directory.
   - Expected Behavior: The test.class file should be put in the subpackage directory.

   Running the java command results in: Exception in thread 'main' java.lang.NoClassDefFoundError: subpackage/Test

3. Running either of the following commands fixes the problem:
   - ajc -d . subpackage\Test.java
   - javac subpackage\Test.java

No big deal, really.
